        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:33PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles west of Raton, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raton.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 64 near Mile Marker 334.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 450 and 457.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
